ResourceHeader.Description: Precipitating electrons and ions observed at nominally 850km altitude and over a range of energies from 30 eV to 30 keV using the Special Sensor J (SSJ) instrument. Please contact Rob.Redmon@noaa.gov with questions and comments. Many individuals made important contributions including: D. Hardy, E. Holeman, F. Rich, D. Ober, G. Wilson, J. Machuzak, K. Kadinsky-Cade, J. McGarity, W.F. Denig, K. Martin, R. Redmon, D. Knipp, L. Kilcommons.

Parameter.Name: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: SC_ECI
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Earth Centered Inertial (ECI) spacecraft location (x,y,z) in km.
Parameter.Caveats: Epoch is True of Date (TOD). These ECI coordinates are calculated from an SPDF SSC Locator 1-minute ephemeris using an 8 order interpolation (Burden, R. L. and Faires, J. D., Numerical Analysis, 5th Ed., PWS Publishing Company, Boston, 1993). Using SPDF methods, expected accuracy is on the order of a few km.

Parameter.Name: SC_GEOCENTRIC_LAT
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: Calculated using IDL Astro Library function eci2geo().

Parameter.Name: SC_GEOCENTRIC_LON
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: Calculated using IDL Astro Library function eci2geo().

Parameter.Name: SC_GEOCENTRIC_RADIUS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Distance from center of Earth in km.

Parameter.Name: SC_AACGM_LAT
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: Calculated using SuperDARN AACGM IDL library. Values are the result of linearly interpolating between 2 nearest AACGM 5-year epochs.

Parameter.Name: SC_AACGM_LON
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: Calculated using SuperDARN AACGM IDL library. Values are the result of linearly interpolating between 2 nearest AACGM 5-year epochs.

Parameter.Name: SC_AACGM_LTIME
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Altitude Adjusted Corrected Geomagnetic Local Time
Parameter.Caveats: Calculated using SuperDARN AACGM IDL library. Values are the result of linearly interpolating between 2 nearest AACGM 5-year epochs.

Parameter.Name: ELE_COUNTS_OBS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Electron counts as observed; no corrections.

Parameter.Name: ELE_COUNTS_BKG
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Caveats: This instrument doesn't have a dedicated background channel. An estimate is arrived at by running the AFRL technique forward and backward in time and choosing the largest of these two estimates for each observation and energy channel.

Parameter.Name: ELE_TOTAL_ENERGY_FLUX_STD
